The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing high-resolution light fields from low-resolution coded measurements using deep learning. This involves tasks such as image processing, computer vision, and machine learning, which are all covered under the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), graphics (cs.GR), multimedia (cs.MM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Given the focus on image reconstruction and deep learning, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.GR and cs.MM. The use of compressive sensing and iterative solutions also suggests a possible fit with cs.SP (signal processing). However, the emphasis on deep learning and neural networks makes cs.LG and cs.AI more likely choices.
